description: {"blocks":[{"key":"d7ogm","text":"Protocol for microscopy-based mtDNA turnover measurements in HeLa and iNeurons","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"c1k4b","text":"Wash HeLa cells expressing doxycycline-inducible Parkin with 1x PBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e4mrb","text":"Add Trypsin to cells for 5 min and incubate at 37°C to dissociate cells from plastic well","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dcoqq","text":"Resuspend cells in 1 mL DMEM media","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8sqh7","text":"Count cells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"38jj8","text":"Seed appropriate number of cells into 24-well glass bottom dish","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8fhtg","text":"Top up glass bottom dish with either 1 mL DMEM and place cells back into incubator","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dla58","text":"The next day exchange DMEM with DMEM + 2µg/ml doxycycline for 18h to induce Parkin expression.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cj7vf","text":"Induce mitophagy using Antimycin A / Oligomycin A for the desired time.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3apdt","text":"Day 0: Treat AAVS1-TRE3G-NGN2 cells with Accutase and plate the dissociated cells in matrigel-coated 6-well plates (2x105 cells/well) in ND1 Medium supplemented with Y27632 (10 μM).  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4jg0g","text":"ND1 Medium:  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bl8vo","text":"DMEM/F12 ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bvbh2","text":"N2 (100x)        1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f0mfj","text":"BDNF              10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3tv1g","text":"NT3                 10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bo5iq","text":"NEAA (100X) 1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"70e0f","text":"Laminin           0.2 μg/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ci85a","text":"Doxycycline    2 μg/ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5u5rc","text":"Day 1: Replace the medium with ND1 Medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9ptua","text":"Day 2: Replace the medium with ND2 Medium.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6q490","text":"ND2 Medium  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"45cp2","text":"Neurobasal medium  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6dc38","text":"B27 (50x)                    1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7tsv8","text":"GlutaMax (100x)         1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7pavq","text":"BDNF                          10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"brl9p","text":"NT3                             10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6g1oh","text":"Doxycycline                2 μg/ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"57sk3","text":"Day 4: Exchange 50% of the medium from each well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ft0nf","text":"Day 6: Treat the cells with Accutase and replate the dissociated cells in matrigel-coated  6-/12-well glass bottom plates (2-4x105 cells/well for 6 wells) in ND2 Medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aapq2","text":"Day 8 and thereafter: Exchange 50% of the medium from each well every other day.  ·       Doxycycline can be withdrawn on Day.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1oi2l","text":"Induce mitophagy using Antimycin A / Oligomycin A for the desired time.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dck7v","text":"Aspirate media and fix cells in 1 ml pre-warmed 4% PFA for 30 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dblbl","text":"Aspirate PFA solution and wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"38qhc","text":"Permeabilize the cells by adding 0.2% Triton X-100 in PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"36g4l","text":"Remove the detergent solution by aspiration.  Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3ua2g","text":"Block cells for 10 min with 3% BSA – 1x PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5qpme","text":"Remove BSA solution by aspiration.  Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2fnie","text":"Incubate with primary antibodies in 3% BSA - 1x PBS for 3h at RT with gentle shaking.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4to12","text":"a.     Anti-DNA (mouse)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1m4c","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"brb8n","text":"Incubate with secondary antibodies in 3% BSA - 1x PBS for 45 min – 1h.  a.     Goat anti-mouse AlexaFlour 488","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5gd6b","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"53ett","text":"Add Hoechst33342 or DAPI 1:2000 to wells for 5 min with gentle shaking.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2a2e5","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ag1u","text":"Exchange PBST with 1x PBS and keep cells at 4°C until imaging. Image within the next few days.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7mud0","text":"Mount glass bottom plate on Yokogawa CSU-W1 spinning disk confocal on a Nikon Eclipse Ti-E motorized microscope equipped with a Nikon Plan Apo 100×/1.45 N.A oil-objective lens. Image signals of 488/568/647 fluorophores in sequential manner with a Nikon LUN-F XL solid state laser combiner ([laser line – laser power]: 488 - 80mW, 561 - 65mW, 640nm - 60mW]) using a Semrock Di01-T405/488/568/647 dichroic mirror. Fluorescence emissions were collected with 488 Chroma ET525/50m [488 nm], 568 Chroma ET605/52m [561 nm], 633 Chroma ET705/72m [640 nm] filters, respectively (Chroma Technologies) using NIS-Elements image acquisition software. Consistent laser intensity and exposure times must be maintained for all samples. Acquire 8 µm z-stacks for each image.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2olji","text":"Image adequate number of cells per repeat in each condition. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"emcfe","text":"Perform image quantification was in your tool of choice. Here we will use ImageJ/FiJi and custom-written batch-macros (https://github.com/harperlaboratory/FBXO7).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"11f37","text":"Filter nuclear signal (Gaussian Blur, sigma=2) and converted images into binary files.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"svqn","text":"Convert aDNA into binary files.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cgq75","text":"Subtract the nuclear signal from the aDNA, resulting in an image containing only the mtDNA intensities.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e8mfs","text":"Measure binary file these masks were using the \"Analyze Particles...\" command (pixel size exclusion: 0.05-3, exclude edge objects)).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6hkpi","text":"Save results image stacks as .csv files, together with the original overlay.tiff file for QC purposes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"foo3n","text":"Count number of nuclei for normalization.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3bqfu","text":"Plot results in your tool of choice for graphing and statistical analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
